dict.string: Call or message contacts and numbers via Alfred

on run tell application "System Events" do shell script "open 'facetime-audio://{query}'" delay 1 click button 1 of group 1 of UI element 1 of scroll area 1 of window 1 of application process "Notification Center" end tell end run

on alfred_script(q)
if application "Contacts" is not running then do shell script "open -j -a 'Contacts.app'" end if
tell application "Contacts" set q to text ((offset of "Metadata/" in q)+9) thru ((offset of "." in q)-1) of q set phonenumber to value of phone of person id q set phonenumber to item 1 of phonenumber end tell
tell application "Contacts" to quit
return phonenumber end alfred_script

on run set q to "{query}" if application "Contacts" is not running then do shell script "open -j -a 'Contacts.app'" end if

on alfred_script(q) tell application "System Events" try try click button "End" of group 1 of UI element 1 of scroll area 1 of window 1 of application process "Notification Center" end try try click button "Cancel" of group 1 of UI element 1 of scroll area 1 of window 1 of application process "Notification Center" end try try click button "Decline" of group 1 of UI element 1 of scroll area 1 of window 1 of application process "Notification Center" end try on error msg return msg end try end tell end alfred_script

# query=$foo # echo -n $query
osascript <<EOD script s on run {targetBuddyPhone, targetMessage} tell application "Messages" set targetService to 1st account whose service type = iMessage set targetBuddy to participant targetBuddyPhone of targetService send targetMessage to targetBuddy end tell end run end script run script s with parameters {"$num", "$message"} EOD

on alfred_script(q) tell application "System Events" try click UI Element "Mute" of group 1 of UI element 1 of scroll area 1 of window 1 of application process "Notification Center" on error return false end try end tell end alfred_script
